You've moved into a typical room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be typical. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen.

You make out a fridge. The fridge is empty! This is the worst thing that could possibly happen, ever! Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's an oven. Classic TextWorld. You see a table. You see a cookbook and a knife on the table. Wow! Just like in the movies! You make out a counter. The counter is vast. But the thing is empty. You see a stove. But the thing hasn't got anything on it.

There is an open screen door leading north. There is an open plain door leading west. There is an exit to the east.
